parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the serpentine belt can cause the loss of power steering, leading to accidents or loss of control, especially at high speeds.
symptoms: The serpentine belt comes off the engine
especially in rainy or snowy conditions
causing loss of power steering
overheating
and potential engine damage.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Transmission failure can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, leading to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The transmission slips out of gear
causing the vehicle to stall or lose power
especially when accelerating or decelerating.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Electrical system failure can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, leading to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The windshield wiper motor fails
the check engine light illuminates
and the vehicle stalls or loses power
especially when driving at high speeds.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine failure can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, leading to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The engine fails
causing the vehicle to stall or lose power
especially when driving at high speeds.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Fuel system failure can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, leading to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The fuel pump fails
causing the vehicle to stall or lose power
especially when driving at high speeds.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the automatic transmission can cause the vehicle to lose power, stall, or become stuck in gear, which can lead to accidents, injuries, or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The transmission fails to shift gears
the vehicle hesitates or jerks when shifting
the transmission slips or hesitates when accelerating
the vehicle stalls or loses power
loud clunking or grinding noises from the transmission
transmission fluid leaks.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Fuel Tank Leaks and Rusted Fuel Filler Neck
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Fuel leaks from the fuel tank and rusted fuel filler neck can cause fires, explosions, and accidents, potentially leading to serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Fuel smell inside the vehicle
fuel leaking from the fuel tank
fuel pouring out from under the car
gas spills when refueling
fuel leaks when the tank is full
fuel leaks from the top of the fuel tank
fuel tank cracking and leaking fuel.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Fuel Rail Leaks and Cross-Over Tube O-Ring Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Fuel rail leaks and cross-over tube O-ring failure can cause fires, explosions, and accidents, potentially leading to serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Fuel smell inside the vehicle
fuel leaking from the fuel rail
fuel rail leaking that could have started a fire under the hood
fuel rail cross-over tube O-ring failure
fuel leaks from the fuel rail.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag clock spring can cause the airbag light to illuminate, rendering the airbag system inoperable, which can lead to serious injury or death in the event of a crash.
symptoms: The airbag light stays on
the horn is inoperative
the cruise control is inoperative
and the airbag system fails to deploy in the event of a crash.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag system to deploy in the event of a crash can lead to serious injury or death.
symptoms: The airbag fails to deploy in the event of a crash
resulting in injury or death.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the cruise control and horn can cause distraction and increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The cruise control is inoperative
and the horn is inoperative or sounds intermittently.
